  "ExtremalPolygonTraits_2": {
    "kind": "class",
    "name": "ExtremalPolygonTraits_2",
    "brief": "This is an advanced concept.",
    "detailed": "Advanced The concept ExtremalPolygonTraits_2 provides the types and operations needed to compute a maximal $ k$ -gon that can be inscribed into a given convex polygon. ExtremalPolygonTraits_2::Less_xy_2 and ExtremalPolygonTraits_2::Orientation_2 are used for (expensive) precondition checking only. Therefore, they need not to be specified, in case that precondition checking is disabled. Has models CGAL::Extremal_polygon_area_traits_2 <K> CGAL::Extremal_polygon_perimeter_traits_2 <K> CGAL::maximum_area_inscribed_k_gon_2() CGAL::maximum_perimeter_inscribed_k_gon_2() CGAL::extremal_polygon_2()",
